      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Excellent! I found very important information:\n\n1. **Event6008**: \"The last unexpected system shutdown occurred at 4:10:28 PM on 7/3/2026\" - This confirms a BSOD happened on July 3rd\n2. **Event 6008**: \"The last unexpected system shutdown occurred at 9:57:32 AM on 7/3/2026\" - Another BSOD on July 3rd morning\n3. **Event 161 (volmgr)**: \"Dump file creation failed due to an error during dump file creation\" - The system couldn't create minidump files, which is why the Minidump folder is empty\n4. **XTU3SERVICE timeout**: Intel XTU (Extreme Tuning Utility) service is failing to start - this is important as XTU is related to CPU overclocking/undervolting\n\nThe system is:\n- Intel Core i5-7300HQ (laptop CPU)\n- HP 838F motherboard (HP laptop)\n- BIOS F.24 from 2021\n- No overclocking possible on this CPU (locked mobile processor)\n\nKey findings:\n- The volmgr error 161 means dump files couldn't be created - this is why there are no minidump files\n- XTU3SERVICE is failing - Intel XTU service may be misconfigured\n- Two BSOD events confirmed on July 3rd\n- No WHEA-Logger events found in the system log (likely because they weren't logged before the crash)\n\nLet me gather more information about:\n1. The page file settings (to ensure dumps can be created)\n2. Storage health\n3. Temperatures\n4. Driver status",
