    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Very interesting findings! Let me get more details on the WHEA events and look at the critical Kernel-Power events. The system shows:\n\n1. Two Kernel-Power 41 (critical) events on July 3rd - these are the BSOD crashes\n2. Corresponding volmgr 161 errors - dump file creation failed\n3. WHEA-Operational log shows many WHEA record entries (event 42) which are WHEA error records\n4. The system uptime was only 89 seconds and 94 seconds after the crashes - meaning the BSOD happened very shortly after boot\n\nThis is very telling - the system crashes almost immediately after booting. Let me dig deeper.",
      "timestamp": 1783146478501
