      "code": "{\"query\": \"best Windows system administration courses Udemy Pluralsight crash dump BSOD analysis 2025\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "Title: System Administration with Windows Server 2025\nURL: https://www.pluralsight.com/courses/system-administration-windows-server-2025\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThis course provides a comprehensive introduction to Windows Server 2025, covering its key features, installation, management tools, and automation ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: Windows Kernel Debugging Fundamentals\nURL: https://www.pluralsight.com/courses/windows-debugging-fundamentals\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n# Windows Kernel Debugging Fundamentals\n...\nWindows developers and IT admins learn valuable skills on debugging the Windows Blue Screen of Death (BSOD). Learn how to use the Windows Debugger (WinDbg), along with knowledge of the internal workings of the Windows operating system as you analyze crashes and hangs.\n...\n# Windows Kernel Debugging Fundamentals\n...\nWindows developers and IT admins learn valuable skills on debugging the Windows Blue Screen of Death (BSOD). Learn how to use the Windows Debugger (WinDbg), along with knowledge of the internal workings of the Windows operating system as you analyze crashes and hangs.\n...\nWindows kernel debugging is one of the most hardcore skills a system administrator can possess. It provides the ability to peer into the workings of the operating system and determine why a server may have crashed or locked up. This course covers the fundamentals essential for understanding the internal workings of the Windows operating system and how to install and use the Windows Debugger. Strategies are provided for examining crashes that give learners immediate confidence with analyzing crashes and hangs. You will learn about Windows processes and threads, stack traces, processors, synchronization mechanisms, address space layout, drivers and interrupts and much more. You will leave this course with the troubleshooting skills that you can leverage for many years to come.\n...\n##### Windows Kernel Debugging Fundamentals\n...\n### Introduction to Windows Crashes and Hangs 27m\n...\nWindows Crashes and Hangs | 2m 31s\n...\n### Getting Started With the Windows Debugger 25m\n...\nPostmortem Analysis | 2m 1s\n...\n### Getting Help in the Windows Debugger 24m\n...\n### Configuring the Windows Debugger 19m\n...\n### Starting Your Crash Dump Analysis 20m\n...\nStarting Your Crash Dump Analysis With the !analyze -v Command | 7m 27s\n...\nDemonstration Using !analyze -v | 6m 29s\n...\nStrategies for Analyzing System Crashes | 3m 35s\n...\nStrategies for Analyzing System Hangs | 3m 23s\n...\n### Understanding Stack Traces 27m\n...\n### Debugging Processes and Threads 29m\n...\n### Understanding Processors and Disassembled Code 28m\n...\n### Investigating Locks and Spinlocks 22m\n...\n### Exploring Windows Virtual Memory 27m\n...\n### Windows Drivers and Interrupts 25m\n...\n### Forcing Windows Memory Dumps 23m\n...\n### 2025 Forrester Wave™ names Pluralsight as a Leader among tech skills dev platforms\n...\nSee how our offering and strategy stack up.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Working with Memory Dumps and Debugging Using Sysinternals Tools\nURL: https://www.pluralsight.com/courses/working-memory-dumps-debugging-sysinternals-tools\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nIn this course, Working with Memory Dumps and Debugging Using Sysinternals Tools, you will gain the ability to debug applications and analyze Blue Screens.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Advanced Troubleshooting Techniques for Windows Server\nURL: https://www.pluralsight.com/courses/advanced-troubleshooting-windows-server\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nAdvanced Troubleshooting Techniques for Windows Server\n...\n# Advanced Troubleshooting Techniques for Windows Server\n...\nSysadmins must know how to resolve Blue Screens of Death, hangs, and performance outages. In this course, real-world demos illustrate techniques, tools, and scripts used to identify buggy drivers, failing hardware, and resource bottlenecks.\n...\nLast Updated Dec 03, 2025\n...\n# Advanced Troubleshooting Techniques for Windows Server\n...\nSysadmins must know how to resolve Blue Screens of Death, hangs, and performance outages. In this course, real-world demos illustrate techniques, tools, and scripts used to identify buggy drivers, failing hardware, and resource bottlenecks.\n...\nLast Updated Dec 03, 2025\n...\n###### Advanced Troubleshooting Techniques for Windows Server\n...\n##### What you'll learn\n...\nUnexpected system outages can challenge even the most seasoned administrators. Knowing what to do and the right tools to use can mean the difference between a few minutes of downtime versus hours or even days of disruption. In this course, Advanced Troubleshooting Techniques for Windows Server, you will learn how to tackle real-world outages. First, you will analyze the most common Blue Screens of Death (BSOD). Then, you will remediate hardware crashes, resolve hangs and lockups, and identify depleted resources and performance bottlenecks. Finally, you will see the best troubleshooting practices and techniques illustrated by over a dozen real-world demonstrations. By the end of this course, you will have the knowledge, skills, and confidence to tackle the toughest outages in your environment.\n...\nAdvanced Troubleshooting Techniques for\n...\n### Analyzing Software Crashes, the Most Common Blue Screen of Death 48m\n...\n### Remediating Hardware Crashes 23m\n...\nTypes of Hardware BSOD | 3m 28s\n...\n### Resolving Hang Timeout Crashes 47m\n...\n### Troubleshooting System Lockups 42m\n...\nHow to Force Memory Dumps | 8m 21s\n...\n### Identifying Depleted System Resources 47m\n...\n38\n...\n### Tackling Performance Outages 21m\n...\n### Using Advanced Troubleshooting Techniques 32m\n...\nTriggering a Crash Based on Perfmon Counters | 1m 51s\n...\nViewing Event Log Entries from Memory Dumps |\n...\n1m 49s\n...\n### Troubleshooting Best Practices 17m\n...\nAnalyzing Crashes and Hangs Best Practices | 4m 57s\n...\n### 2025 Forrester Wave™ names Pluralsight as a Leader among tech skills dev platforms\n\n---\n\nTitle: Windows Server 2025 Administration\nURL: https://www.pluralsight.com/paths/windows-server-2025-administration\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThis learning path covers everything you'll need to confidently handle Windows Server 2025 administration, no matter if you're sticking to on-prem or exploring ...",
